01:11:36,625 --> 01:11:38,495
[Cheering]

1531
01:11:38,527 --> 01:11:41,398
[Joy to the world playing]

1532
01:11:47,670 --> 01:11:48,572
What's up there?

1533
01:11:48,604 --> 01:11:51,441
Santa, I love Christmas.

1534
01:11:51,475 --> 01:11:53,910
I know you do.

1535
01:11:55,110 --> 01:11:56,712
High-five.

1536
01:11:56,745 --> 01:11:57,447
Yeah!

1537
01:11:57,481 --> 01:11:59,782
It's beautiful.

1538
01:11:59,816 --> 01:12:02,852
I'm tellin' you,
there is nothin' to worry about.

1539
01:12:02,886 --> 01:12:06,456
Because 50 grand is a lot
of money to these people.

1540
01:12:06,489 --> 01:12:08,791
There's no way
they're gonna raise it

1541
01:12:08,825 --> 01:12:11,794
Sellin' reindeer rides
and fruitcake.

1542
01:12:19,602 --> 01:12:20,469
I will.

1543
01:12:20,504 --> 01:12:22,439
I'll keep you posted.

1544
01:12:35,419 --> 01:12:36,652
There he is.

1545
01:12:36,685 --> 01:12:39,423
Come on, guys.
Santa's right up here.

1546
01:12:39,456 --> 01:12:40,924
You can go see him.

1547
01:12:40,957 --> 01:12:42,426
Watch the train right here.

1548
01:12:42,459 --> 01:12:44,561
Santa's right... right up there.
Keep going.

1549
01:12:44,593 --> 01:12:46,530
Keep going. Santa's there.

1550
01:12:46,563 --> 01:12:48,465
Hi!

1551
01:12:48,498 --> 01:12:51,800
Hey, tried calling.

1552
01:12:52,936 --> 01:12:55,103
Come on, holly.

1553
01:12:55,671 --> 01:12:57,407
It was just business.

1554
01:12:57,441 --> 01:12:58,707
Just business?

1555
01:12:58,741 --> 01:13:00,944
Swindling my father
out of his home?

1556
01:13:00,977 --> 01:13:03,679
Out of his life savings?
That's just business?

1557
01:13:03,712 --> 01:13:05,482
Come on. You're a smart girl.

1558
01:13:05,515 --> 01:13:07,517
You're not like
the rest of these locals.

1559
01:13:07,550 --> 01:13:11,186
Hey, you understand the way
things work in the real world.

1560
01:13:11,220 --> 01:13:13,422
No, not this way, not for me.

1561
01:13:13,457 --> 01:13:15,424
What do you want me to say?

1562
01:13:15,459 --> 01:13:16,525
"I'm sorry"?

1563
01:13:16,559 --> 01:13:17,593
Fine. Sorry.

1564
01:13:17,627 --> 01:13:19,195
Sorry doesn't feed the cat.

1565
01:13:19,228 --> 01:13:20,396
And come Christmas Eve,

1566
01:13:20,430 --> 01:13:23,433
You're still not gonna have
enough money to save this place.

1567
01:13:23,467 --> 01:13:24,800
You were here last night.

1568
01:13:24,833 --> 01:13:28,170
You saw the crowds.
They're comin' back.

1569
01:13:28,204 --> 01:13:29,005
Ok, look,

1570
01:13:29,037 --> 01:13:31,140
There's no reason
you and your father

1571
01:13:31,173 --> 01:13:33,777
Have to walk away
from this empty-handed, ok?

1572
01:13:33,809 --> 01:13:36,212
[Scoffs] Are you...
Are you trying to bribe me?

1573
01:13:36,244 --> 01:13:38,647
No. That's not what I meant.

1574
01:13:38,682 --> 01:13:40,883
We must have you
really nervous, Ben.

1575
01:13:40,917 --> 01:13:41,784
What's the matter?

1576
01:13:41,817 --> 01:13:44,020
Afraid you're gonna lose
your finder's fee?

1577
01:13:44,053 --> 01:13:47,056
Heh. Was just tryin'
to do you a favor.

1578
01:13:47,090 --> 01:13:49,825
Yeah, I've had enough
of your favors.

1579
01:13:49,858 --> 01:13:51,561
This place is my home.

1580
01:13:51,595 --> 01:13:55,565
Your heartless soul
isn't welcome here anymore.

1581
01:13:55,599 --> 01:13:57,165
Get out.

1582
01:13:57,200 --> 01:14:00,069
You can't win this, holly.

1583
01:14:02,005 --> 01:14:04,440
You know that.

1584
01:14:14,082 --> 01:14:15,752
I was out there
with my grandkids,

1585
01:14:15,785 --> 01:14:17,219
And we had a wonderful time.

1586
01:14:17,253 --> 01:14:19,622
They just loved it.
It was so magical.

1587
01:14:19,655 --> 01:14:20,490
That's great, Mr. corwell,

1588
01:14:20,524 --> 01:14:22,559
Because we're
kind of in a crunch here.

1589
