Mr. Richards came by
to introduce himself
to me a few days ago.

1590
01:14:25,594 --> 01:14:27,663
Then I don't need to tell you
what's at stake.

1591
01:14:27,697 --> 01:14:30,567
If you could use the money
we've made so far

1592
01:14:30,599 --> 01:14:31,968
As a kind of good-faith payment

1593
01:14:32,001 --> 01:14:34,003
To secure the rest
of what we need...

1594
01:14:34,037 --> 01:14:36,506
You've deposited
nearly $28,000,

1595
01:14:36,540 --> 01:14:37,607
And that's very impressive,

1596
01:14:37,641 --> 01:14:41,077
But it still leaves you
with a substantial debt load.

1597
01:14:41,110 --> 01:14:42,911
People are coming
from all over.

1598
01:14:42,945 --> 01:14:44,947
We still have 4 days
before Christmas.

1599
01:14:44,981 --> 01:14:47,617
And then there's January,
which as you know,

1600
01:14:47,651 --> 01:14:50,119
Is the slowest month
for any holiday business.

1601
01:14:50,153 --> 01:14:52,888
This property has been
the lifeblood of my family.

1602
01:14:52,921 --> 01:14:56,626
My father cannot lose this.
I won't let it happen.

1603
01:14:56,660 --> 01:14:58,528
I'm sorry, holly.

1604
01:14:58,562 --> 01:15:01,164
I am, too.

1605
01:15:01,565 --> 01:15:03,132
I forgot how great it was

1606
01:15:03,166 --> 01:15:06,302
To have all those little
smilin' faces runnin' around.

1607
01:15:06,335 --> 01:15:10,540
Yeah. It really brought
the old place back to life.

1608
01:15:10,574 --> 01:15:12,275
Turns out people do remember

1609
01:15:12,307 --> 01:15:15,277
With a little help
from your awesome plan.

1610
01:15:15,311 --> 01:15:18,882
Oh. Well, we... we wouldn't have
gotten anywhere without Peter.

1611
01:15:18,915 --> 01:15:22,686
Yeah. You and Peter
make a good team.

1612
01:15:26,288 --> 01:15:27,390
I read your blog.

1613
01:15:27,422 --> 01:15:29,958
Today was really sweet,
the way the encouraged the kids

1614
01:15:29,992 --> 01:15:31,927
To give a toy to a needy child.

1615
01:15:31,960 --> 01:15:34,097
Yeah. Yeah,
it was sweet and...

1616
01:15:34,130 --> 01:15:35,198
Took a long time.

1617
01:15:35,230 --> 01:15:36,666
You know, that reminds me,

1618
01:15:36,700 --> 01:15:38,234
Uh, all the kids are back now,

1619
01:15:38,266 --> 01:15:41,003
A-and they've all got
long lists for Santa,

1620
01:15:41,037 --> 01:15:43,271
And Santa's busy,
and he was wondering

1621
01:15:43,306 --> 01:15:46,942
If maybe his daughter could
take over the blog and...

1622
01:15:46,975 --> 01:15:47,811
For a little while.

1623
01:15:47,843 --> 01:15:49,613
Don't you mean
Santa's number-one elf?

1624
01:15:49,646 --> 01:15:50,478
No. Santa has a daughter,

1625
01:15:50,512 --> 01:15:54,217
And it's time the world
got to know her.

1626
01:15:55,251 --> 01:15:56,753
- I'd love to.
- Thank you.

1627
01:15:56,785 --> 01:15:59,122
Ok, dad,
why don't you go to bed.

1628
01:15:59,155 --> 01:16:00,923
I'll... i can finish up here.

1629
01:16:00,956 --> 01:16:02,925
Well...

1630
01:16:02,958 --> 01:16:03,491
Ok.

1631
01:16:03,525 --> 01:16:04,560
- Ok.
- Night, honey.

1632
01:16:04,560 --> 01:16:06,295
Good night.

1633
