01:23:09,084 --> 01:23:11,354
'Cause I got
a previous engagement.

1783
01:23:11,387 --> 01:23:14,357
You know, you should
really be in bed, too.

1784
01:23:14,390 --> 01:23:16,292
[Scattered laughter]

1785
01:23:16,325 --> 01:23:18,461
Uh, before Santa leaves,

1786
01:23:18,494 --> 01:23:21,396
There's something
I wanna say to you.

1787
01:23:21,429 --> 01:23:25,168
I grew up here,
and every memory I have

1788
01:23:25,200 --> 01:23:30,673
Is connected to this place
and all of the people in it.

1789
01:23:31,139 --> 01:23:33,076
I went away for a while,

1790
01:23:33,109 --> 01:23:34,442
A long while,

1791
01:23:34,476 --> 01:23:37,280
Because I was convinced
that all the love

1792
01:23:37,312 --> 01:23:41,284
And kindness and generosity that
I remembered from this place

1793
01:23:41,316 --> 01:23:44,153
Was a thing of the past.

1794
01:23:44,187 --> 01:23:47,156
And I know now how wrong I was,

1795
01:23:47,190 --> 01:23:49,357
Thanks to you...

1796
01:23:49,391 --> 01:23:50,458
And all of you.

1797
01:23:50,492 --> 01:23:54,597
There still is a place
where people care in this world,

1798
01:23:54,630 --> 01:23:56,498
Where they wanna help.

1799
01:23:56,532 --> 01:23:59,802
And that's why you're all here,

1800
01:23:59,834 --> 01:24:02,270
Because you remember, too,

1801
01:24:02,305 --> 01:24:06,374
And you wanted to keep
this one magical place

1802
01:24:06,409 --> 01:24:08,576
Open for the next generation.

1803
01:24:08,611 --> 01:24:09,578
Yeah.

1804
01:24:09,612 --> 01:24:10,278
Right.

1805
01:24:10,313 --> 01:24:12,448
But we didn't reach our goal,

1806
01:24:12,480 --> 01:24:15,784
So this'll be the last Christmas
for santaville.

1807
01:24:15,817 --> 01:24:17,652
[Moans]

1808
01:24:19,821 --> 01:24:21,323
It was going so well.

1809
01:24:21,357 --> 01:24:22,658
Honey, it's ok. We tried.

1810
01:24:22,690 --> 01:24:27,130
We tried really hard,
but we came up a little short.

1811
01:24:27,163 --> 01:24:28,463
It's over now.

1812
01:24:28,496 --> 01:24:29,798
I love you.

1813
01:24:29,831 --> 01:24:33,768
Holly! Holly, wait!

1814
01:24:35,403 --> 01:24:36,271
Mr. Jennings?

1815
01:24:36,305 --> 01:24:38,574
Brenda showed me
the santaville website.

1816
01:24:38,607 --> 01:24:39,342
The woodcarvings are...

1817
01:24:39,374 --> 01:24:41,443
We think
they're just wonderful.

1818
01:24:41,476 --> 01:24:42,778
And so do our customers.

1819
01:24:42,810 --> 01:24:47,415
I wanna make global
handcrafts the exclusive
distributor, holly.

1820
01:24:47,449 --> 01:24:49,352
With you running things
up here,

1821
01:24:49,384 --> 01:24:52,188
We could sell 'em
all over the world.

1822
01:24:52,221 --> 01:24:53,455
But they're... they're not mine.

1823
01:24:53,488 --> 01:24:55,191
Um, Mr. Jennings,
this is Peter lowdell.

1824
01:24:55,224 --> 01:24:56,792
He's the artist.
He made all of these.

1825
01:24:56,824 --> 01:24:59,827
Love your work, Peter.
What do you say? You interested?

1826
01:24:59,862 --> 01:25:02,330
Well, you know
I carve these by hand.

1827
01:25:02,365 --> 01:25:04,267
They don't come from a factory.

1828
01:25:04,300 --> 01:25:06,202
Wouldn't want it
any other way.

1829
01:25:06,235 --> 01:25:08,403
And my shop
would have to stay here.

1830
01:25:08,437 --> 01:25:09,472
You could sell them online,

1831
01:25:09,505 --> 01:25:12,407
But I wanna make sure
everyone knows that santaville

1832
01:25:12,441 --> 01:25:14,577
Is the only place
you can buy them in person.

1833
01:25:14,610 --> 01:25:17,513
Wouldn't have it
any other way.

1834
01:25:18,681 --> 01:25:20,748
Peter, are you sure?

1835
01:25:22,718 --> 01:25:26,189
I never would've made them
if it wasn't for this place.

1836
01:25:26,222 --> 01:25:29,891
If it's what you want,
it's what I want.

1837
01:25:31,259 --> 01:25:33,496
Mr. Jennings,
you can tell our customers

1838
01:25:33,528 --> 01:25:36,531
That I'll be
looking after things up here

1839
01:25:36,564 --> 01:25:37,532
Personally.

1840
01:25:37,565 --> 01:25:38,634
Young man,

1841
01:25:38,667 --> 01:25:42,437
I think you're going to be
very busy for quite a while.

1842
01:25:42,470 --> 01:25:44,506
In the meantime,
how many do you have left?

1843
01:25:44,539 --> 01:25:47,542
- Um, none.
- We're... we sold out.

1844
01:25:47,575 --> 01:25:51,214
Well, you could
commission one...

1845
01:25:51,247 --> 01:25:54,417
For say, $8,000.

1846
01:25:54,449 --> 01:25:55,684
Yeah. Is that legal?

1847
01:25:55,718 --> 01:25:57,320
You bet it is...

1848
01:25:57,353 --> 01:25:59,887
For another 4 minutes.

1849
01:25:59,922 --> 01:26:01,424
Done.

1850
01:26:01,456 --> 01:26:02,590
Yes!

1851
01:26:02,624 --> 01:26:03,726
Right!

1852
01:26:03,759 --> 01:26:07,562
[Cheering]

1853
01:26:09,732 --> 01:26:11,367
Wait.

1854
01:26:11,399 --> 01:26:13,736
Merry Christmas after all.

1855
01:26:13,768 --> 01:26:14,936
Merry Christmas.

1856
01:26:14,970 --> 01:26:16,204
Ok.

1857
01:26:16,239 --> 01:26:19,941
[Cheering and applause]

1858
01:26:24,512 --> 01:26:27,449
[Narrating] Christmas was
always different for me.

1859
01:26:27,483 --> 01:26:30,452
It was always better.
I just forgot that for a while.

1860
01:26:30,486 --> 01:26:33,256
Dad and Ginny run santaville
together now.

1861
01:26:33,289 --> 01:26:34,656
Peter and I were married there,

1862
01:26:34,690 --> 01:26:37,492
Complete with moonlight
and mistletoe.

1863
01:26:37,525 --> 01:26:39,328
And by the next Christmas,

1864
01:26:39,362 --> 01:26:41,697
Santa will have
a new little elf to train.

1865
01:26:41,730 --> 01:26:45,334
So don't forget to come and
visit all of us at santaville,

1866
01:26:45,368 --> 01:26:47,669
Where every day
truly is Christmas.

1867
01:26:47,703 --> 01:26:50,638
From Santa's
loving daughter, holly.

1868
01:26:50,672 --> 01:26:55,344
* ...And a happy new year

